claim.claim-text:
A method of controlling a sleep mode in a portable terminal having a main controller and a sub-controller operating at low power, the method comprising:
detecting, by the sub-controller, a first sensor signal generated by a first sensor when the main controller is in a sleep mode;
extracting a sensed pattern from the detected first sensor signal;
comparing the extracted sensed pattern to a preset wake-up pattern; and
cancelling the sleep mode by waking-up the main controller depending on the outcome of the comparison between the extracted sensed pattern and the wake-up pattern.

The method of any one of the preceding claims, further comprising:
receiving, by the sub-controller, a second sensor signal;
determining whether the received second sensor signal satisfies a preset alarm condition;
cancelling the sleep mode by waking-up the main controller when the alarm condition is satisfied;
limiting some of functions of the portable terminal when the alarm condition is satisfied; and
reporting an alarm notifying that some functions of the portable terminal are limited.

An apparatus for controlling a sleep mode in a portable terminal, the apparatus comprising;

a main controller arranged to request entering the sleep mode;

a first sensor arranged to detect a first sensor signal when the main controller is in the sleep mode; and

a sub-controller arranged to operate at a low power;

wherein the sub-controller is further arranged to be activated to extract a sensed pattern from the first sensor signal detected by the first sensor when the main controller is in the sleep mode, and to wake-up the main controller depending on a comparison between the extracted sensed pattern and a preset wake-up pattern.

The apparatus of claim 9, wherein the camera comprises a plurality of pixels;

wherein a subset of the plurality of pixels are arranged to activate in the sleep mode; and

wherein the camera is further arranged to connect to the sub-controller through a low speed interface.
